[1] Current CDC statistics
Date: Fri 19 Oct 2012
Source: CDC [edited]
http://www.cdc.gov/HAI/outbreaks/meningitis.html


As of 17 Oct 2012, a total of 47 patients have laboratory-confirmed fungal meningitis. This form of fungal meningitis is not contagious. CDC's laboratory has confirmed _Exserohilum rostratum_ in clinical specimens for all but 2 patients of these patients. Of the other 2 patients, one has been found to be infected with _Aspergillus fumigatus_ and one with _Cladosporium_. These fungi are common in the environment but rarely cause meningitis.

At-A-Glance
Status: Ongoing Investigation
Infection: Fungal
Facility Type: Outpatient Setting
Case Count: 271
States: 16
Deaths: 21

